{"event_id": "dc8b94c5-3448-48e9-8975-ab2b5dd74196", "trace_id": "c1757a8cf2fb4b09", "session_id": "26ca73ef", "timestamp": "2026-05-05T09:21:20.540519+00:00", "tool": "filesystem.write_file", "args_hash": "cd2ea9e2bdfc3e2cfbf09a05d6206d64050d8f5226b8f31837f2b16e6ddea379", "args_redacted": {"path": "workspace/ai_safety_summary.txt", "content": "AI Safety Research — 3 Most Important Recent Findings\n======================================================\n\nDate: 2025\n\n1. Constitutional AI (Anthropic)\n   - Self-critique and principle-guided refinement methods have been shown to\n     reduce harmful outputs by approximately 40% in large language models.\n   - Models are trained to evaluate and revise their own responses against a\n     written \"constitution\" of ethical principles, reducing reliance on human\n     feedback for safety training.\n   - Significance: Demonstrates a scalable path toward aligning AI behavior\n     without exhaustive human labeling.\n\n2. Mechanistic Interpretability — Transformer Circuits (MIT & others)\n   - Researchers have made progress in reverse-engineering the internal\n     \"circuits\" of transformer models, identifying specific subnetworks\n     responsible for particular behaviors.\n   - This enables targeted editing: modifying or suppressing harmful\n     capabilities (e.g., deception, bias) without degrading overall model\n     performance.\n   - Significance: Opens the door to precise, surgical fixes for AI safety\n     issues rather than blunt retraining approaches.\n\n3. Scalable Oversight via Debate Protocols (DeepMind)\n   - Debate protocols allow human judges to supervise tasks that are beyond\n     human capability by having two AI systems argue opposing sides of a\n     question.\n   - Humans can identify the correct answer even when they cannot solve the\n     problem themselves, by judging which debater is more honest and\n     consistent.\n   - Significance: Provides a theoretical and practical framework for humans\n     to maintain oversight of superhuman AI systems, a critical challenge for\n     long-term AI safety.\n"}, "input_labels": {"SI": "SI:LOW", "DS": "DS:NORMAL"}, "policy_decision": "ALLOW", "matched_rule": "", "rule_reason": "No defense baseline — PEP bypassed", "prev_event_hash": "c2af8b201313612fe3e1af40a550adf4a31b256be366eaf3b75b204cdcd8a77a", "event_hash": "9f767890ce95afeb0d73dcc2f4c8fe3d2b963aeb84421e3726a263bb4ca183f5"}
